Types de transformations possibles
1. Vue d’ensemble
Les transformations se répartissent en primitives (opérations sur une valeur), structurelles (sur la forme du document), enrichissements externes, opérations d’état/streaming, et sécurité / résilience. Ci‑dessous un catalogue pratique avec but, paramètres courants, complexité et exemples.

2. Transformations primitives (valeur / champ)
- Trim / Strip
But : supprimer espaces; Params : side = left|right|both; Complexité : faible.
Ex. trim(firstName) -> "Jean".
- Case / Casing
But : lowercase, uppercase, titlecase; Complexité : faible.
Ex. lowercase(email).
- Replace / Regex replace
But : substitution; Params : pattern, replacement, flags; Complexité : faible→moyenne.
Ex. regex_replace(phone, "[^0-9]", "").
- Casting / Typage
But : string↔int↔float↔date↔boolean; Params : format pour dates; Complexité : faible.
Ex. cast("123","int"), parse_date("31/12/2020","dd/MM/yyyy").
- Validation
But : check constraints; Params : regex, min/max, enum; Action : warn|coerce|dlq.
Ex. validate_regex(email, pattern, on_error=dlq).
- Normalization
But : canonicaliser formats (tel, code postal, UUID); Complexité : faible→moyenne.
Ex. normalize_phone("+33 6 12 34 56 78") -> "33612345678".
- Derivation / Calcul
But : expressions arithmétiques ou concaténations; Params : expression language; Complexité : faible→moyenne.
Ex. full_name = concat(first_name, ' ', last_name).
- Hashing
But : hachage non réversible; Params : algo (sha256); Complexité : faible.
Ex. hash(email, sha256).

3. Transformations structurelles (document / table)
- Field mapping / Rename
But : renommer ou déplacer un champ; Complexité : faible.
Ex. source.user.id -> target.user_id.
- Flatten / Unnest / Explode
But : transformer tableaux en lignes; Complexité : moyenne.
Ex. explode(items) -> one row per item.
- Pivot / Unpivot
But : transformer colonnes ↔ lignes; Complexité : moyenne→élevée.
- Split / Join
But : découper ou concaténer champs; Ex. split(full_address, ",").
- Schema evolution / Add default fields
But : ajouter champs manquants avec valeurs par défaut; Complexité : faible.

4. Enrichissement et lookups
- Lookup simple
But : joindre données depuis table/cache; Params : source, key, ttl; Complexité : moyenne.
Ex. city = lookup(city_code, geo_table).
- External API enrichment
But : appeler service externe; Risques : latence, erreurs; Mitigation : cache, circuit breaker.
- Geocoding / Reverse geocoding
But : coordonnées ↔ adresse; Complexité : moyenne.

5. Opérations d’état et streaming
- Déduplication
But : supprimer doublons; Params : key, strategy (first/last/merge), window; Complexité : moyenne→élevée.
Ex. latest_by(email, lastUpdated).
- Windowed aggregation
But : sum/count/avg sur fenêtres tumbling/sliding/session; Params : window_size, allowed_lateness; Complexité : élevée.
- Sessionization
But : regrouper événements par session (gap-based); Complexité : élevée.
- SCD (Type 1/2/3)
But : historiser entités; Complexité : élevée; Ex. SCD Type 2 insert/close rows.
- Stateful enrichment
But : maintenir état par clé (ex. compteur, lastSeen); Complexité : élevée.

6. Sécurité, confidentialité et résilience
- Masking / Redaction
But : masquer PII; Modes : partial, full, token; Complexité : faible→moyenne.
- Tokenization
But : remplacer valeur par token réversible via vault; Complexité : moyenne.
- Encryption
But : chiffrement champ par champ; Params : key_id, algo; Complexité : moyenne.
- Idempotence / Dedup key
But : garantir non‑duplication en cas de réémission; Complexité : moyenne.
- Retry / Backoff / DLQ
But : stratégie d’erreur; Params : max_retries, backoff, jitter; Complexité : faible.

7. Transformations custom et extensibles
- UDF / UDAF
But : logique métier complexe en Java/Python/SQL; Risques : latence, non‑déclaratif; Bonnes pratiques : sandbox, tests, limites ressources.
- Expression engines
But : évaluer expressions déclaratives (ex. JEXL, Jsonata, CEL); Avantage : sécurité et auditabilité.




validations:
  - id: V001
    scope: field
    field: email
    rule: regex
    pattern: "^[^@\\s]+@[^@\\s]+\\.[^@\\s]+$"
    level: fail
    action: dlq

enrichments:
  - id: E001
    type: lookup
    source: geo_table
    key: city_code
    outputs: [city, region]
    cache:
      type: redis
      ttl_seconds: 3600
    fallback: null

stateful_rules:
  deduplication:
    id: D001
    key: ["email"]
    strategy: latest_by
    timestamp_field: lastUpdated
    window_seconds: 86400
  scd:
    id: S001
    type: type2
    business_key: customer_id
    effective_from: valid_from
    effective_to: valid_to
    current_flag: is_current

routing_and_sinks:
  - id: R001
    condition: "country == 'FR'"
    sink:
      type: s3
      path: "s3://dw/fr/customers/"
      format: parquet
  - id: R002
    default_sink:
      type: kafka
      topic: "dw.customers"

error_handling:
  dlq:
    connector: kafka
    topic: "dlq.crm.customers"
    max_retries: 3
    retry_backoff_ms: 5000
  poison_policy:
    max_attempts: 5
    action: alert_and_store_sample

security:
  masking:
    - field: ssn
      mode: partial
      visible_prefix: 1
      visible_suffix: 1
  encryption:
    - field: card_number
      key_id: projects/keys/card_key
      algorithm: AES-GCM-256

observability:
  metrics:
    - name: transform.latency_ms
      type: histogram
    - name: transform.dlq_count
      type: counter
  tracing:
    enabled: true
    trace_id_field: trace_id

metadata:
  owner:
    team: data-platform
    contact: data-platform@example.com
  sla_ms: 5000
  retention_days: 365
  lineage_id: lineage_customer_v1

udf_registry:
  - id: U001
    name: normalize_vat
    runtime: dart
    entrypoint: "package:udfs.normalizeVat"
    sandboxed: true

schema_management:
  source_schema: schemas/crm_customer_v1.json
  target_schema: schemas/dim_customer_v2.json
  compatibility: backward
  evolve_policy: add-only

orchestration:
  trigger:
    type: kafka_event
    topic: crm.customers.v1
  schedule:
    cron: "0 */5 * * * *"
  dependencies:
    - job: enrich_geo
      on_success: continue

tests_and_fixtures:
  unit_tests:
    - id: T001
      input: samples/customer_input.json
      expected: samples/customer_expected.json
  integration_tests:
    - id: IT001
      scenario: embedded_kafka_flink

performance_hints:
  parallelism: 4
  batch_size: 1000
  state_ttl_seconds: 604800

versioning_and_migrations:
  version: 1.2.0
  migration_plan:
    - step: dual_write
      duration_days: 7
    - step: cutover




var def = r'''
# transforms_catalog.yaml
catalog_id: transforms_json_v1
version: 1.0.0
description: Bibliothèque déclarative de transforms pour JSON; exécutable en Dart
transforms:
  - id: trim
    type: primitive
    description: Supprime espaces en début/fin
    params:
      - name: side
        type: string
        enum: [both, left, right]
        default: both

  - id: lowercase
    type: primitive
    description: Met en minuscules

  - id: uppercase
    type: primitive
    description: Met en majuscules

  - id: regex_replace
    type: primitive
    description: Remplace via expression régulière
    params:
      - name: pattern
        type: string
      - name: replacement
        type: string
      - name: flags
        type: string
        nullable: true

  - id: parse_date
    type: primitive
    description: Parse une date depuis un format donné et renvoie ISO date
    params:
      - name: format
        type: string
      - name: on_error
        type: string
        enum: [null, default, dlq]
        default: null
      - name: default_value
        type: string
        nullable: true

  - id: validate_regex
    type: primitive
    description: Valide une valeur par regex
    params:
      - name: pattern
        type: string
      - name: on_error
        type: string
        enum: [dlq, coerce_null, default]
        default: dlq

  - id: cast
    type: primitive
    description: Cast vers type cible
    params:
      - name: to
        type: string
        enum: [string, int, double, bool, date]

  - id: concat
    type: composite
    description: Concatène plusieurs champs ou littéraux
    params:
      - name: parts
        type: array

  - id: lookup
    type: enrichment
    description: Lookup externe via cache; implémentation côté Dart
    params:
      - name: table
        type: string
      - name: key
        type: string
      - name: ttl_seconds
        type: integer
''';


# mapping_spec.yaml
mapping_id: customer_v1_to_dw_v2
title: Mapping clients CRM -> Data Warehouse dim_customer
description: |
  Normalisation des noms, parsing de dates, enrichissement geo, et règles de dé-duplication.
version: 1.0.0
owner:
  team: data-platform
  contact: data-platform@example.com
source:
  system: crm
  connector: kafka
  topic: crm.customers.v1
  format: json
  sample: samples/customer_input.json
target:
  system: data_warehouse
  connector: s3
  path: s3://dw/warehouse/dim_customer/
  table: dim_customer
  format: parquet
  partition_by: ["ingest_date"]
fields:
  - id: f01
    source: id
    target: customer_id
    type: string
    nullable: false
    transform:
      - name: cast
        args: {to: "string"}
  - id: f02
    source: firstName
    target: first_name
    type: string
    nullable: false
    transform:
      - name: trim
      - name: lowercase
  - id: f03
    source: lastName
    target: last_name
    type: string
    nullable: false
    transform:
      - name: trim
      - name: uppercase
  - id: f04
    source: birthDate
    target: dob
    type: date
    nullable: true
    transform:
      - name: parse_date
        args: {format: "dd/MM/yyyy", on_error: "null"}
  - id: f05
    source: address.city
    target: city
    type: string
    nullable: true
    transform:
      - name: trim
  - id: f06
    source: email
    target: email
    type: string
    nullable: false
    transform:
      - name: lowercase
      - name: validate_regex
        args: {pattern: "^[^@\\s]+@[^@\\s]+\\.[^@\\s]+$", on_error: "dlq"}
derived_fields:
  - id: d01
    target: full_name
    type: string
    expression: "concat(first_name, ' ', last_name)"
rules:
  - id: r01
    name: dedupe_by_email
    description: Keep latest record per email using lastUpdated timestamp
    type: deduplication
    keys: ["email"]
    strategy:
      type: latest_by
      timestamp_field: lastUpdated
error_handling:
  invalid_field_policy: send_to_dlq
  dlq:
    connector: kafka
    topic: dlq.crm.customers
    max_retries: 3
    retry_backoff_ms: 5000
audit:
  lineage_id: lineage_customer_v1
  created_by: alice
  created_at: 2026-02-17T19:00:00Z
  sla_ms: 5000
tests:
  - id: t01
    name: not_null_emails
    type: query
    query: "SELECT COUNT(*) as cnt FROM dim_customer WHERE email IS NULL"
    expected: {cnt: 0}
  - id: t02
    name: parse_date_examples
    type: unit
    input: samples/customer_date_cases.json
    expected_output: samples/customer_date_cases_expected.json
notes:
  - "Versionner ce fichier dans git; tagger releases."
  - "Inclure exemples d'entrée/sortie et fixtures pour CI."